The founder of Kingsway International Christian Centre (KICC) Pastor Matthew Ashimolowo has appointed his first son, Tobi Ashimolowo, as Resident Pastor 2 of the church in London. He is expected to assist his mother, Yemisi Ashimolowo, who is the Resident Pastor 1. Tobi is the Founder and Chief Executive Officer of the Vault, a high-end store for mens wear and accessories.   Positioning agric to drive economic growth     No extension for capital market operators’ registration,…     Equities record N1.899tr deals   In the now-viral undated video, Ashimolowo hinted at his ‘retirement’ during the announcement of his son’s new role. He said: “In a very major way from this morning, we will no longer have one resident pastor. - Advertisement - “Yemisi has always been our resident pastor, so she will be Resident Pastor 1. Our new resident pastor is Pastor Tobi Ashimolowo. “So, he is our Resident Pastor 2, he has to take some serious responsibility from now on. These guys are retiring their father.”